<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="ribozyme">Ribozyme</a> - An <a href="#rna">RNA molecule</a> that is capable of <a href="#catalysation">catalysing</a> chemical reactions. Many ribozymes of interest (hammerhead and hairpin) <a href="#catalysation">catalyse</a> <a href="#rna">RNA</a> <a href="#cleavage">cleavage</a> and <a href="#ligation">ligation</a> reactions.